size: the second and third copies become long back-references.

Note on the token format: our `encode`/`decode` functions use a simple 5-byte
format per match token (1 flag + 2 distance bytes + 2 length bytes) for
clarity and testing. This is *not* the DEFLATE bit format. Chapter 30 will
replace this with the bit-packed (length code, distance code) representation
from RFC 1951, using the Huffman machinery from Chapter 24.
